Such records shall bemaintained and if a non-conformity is reported three times in a year, against any particular supplier, his services shall not be utilized.Each vessel shall maintain an inventory of stores and spare parts onboard which shall be kept updated.Record of consumption and ROB quantities of all stores and spares, including lubricating oils, chemicals and gases, shall be recordedin Phoenix by the concerned officers.5.8INVOICES AND PAYMENTS5.9OUTSOURCINGAn outsourced process is a process that the company needs for its HSEQA System and which the company chooses to haveperformed by a vendor totally independent from the company or by an entity which is part of the same parent organisation. It mayinvolve subcontracting of a process, such as shipâ€™s audit, vessel inspection or training of seafarers. It may be provided within thephysical premises or work environment of the company or its managed ships, at an independent site or in some other manner. Thedecision to outsource is often made in the interest of making better use of time and energy costs, redirecting or conserving energydirected at the competencies of a particular entity.In case the Company chooses to outsource a process identified by the Company as a requirement for its HSEQA System, proceduresoutlined below shall be followed. Any outsourced processes must be identified and controlled.1) In case the Company has the competence and ability to carry out the process, control criteria shall be as per the relevant section ofthe HSEQA System.In this situation the process control criteria should already have been defined by company and can be transposed into requirements
